Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.30,0:02:00.60,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:119307,120600}How did I…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.14,0:02:03.10,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:122143,123102}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.10,0:02:06.73,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:123102,126731}How did I get in my bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.73,0:02:09.23,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:126731,129233}I think something\Nhappened yesterday…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.31,0:02:12.23,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:130318,132236}Ah, right! That puppy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.55,0:02:35.46,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:154550,155468}Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.46,0:02:36.96,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:155468,156969}Good morning, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.96,0:02:37.84,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:156969,157845}You woke up early.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.84,0:02:39.47,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:157845,159472}Yes, you too, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.05,0:02:43.55,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:160056,163559}Hey, this is not a breast.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.55,0:02:46.14,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:163559,166145}Wait a moment.\NI'll bring you some fresh milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.40,0:02:52.56,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:171401,172568}Hey there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.56,0:02:53.86,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:172568,173861}Would you like some soup?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.77,0:02:55.40,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:174779,175405}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.40,0:02:56.86,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:175405,176864}No, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.53,0:03:01.61,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:177532,181619}She's like a baby,\Nshe can only drink from a bottle.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.61,0:03:03.37,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:181619,183371}I… I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.37,0:03:10.67,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:188376,190670}You look like its mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.79,0:03:15.34,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:192797,195341}Hey, how about "Shorty"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.34,0:03:16.34,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:195341,196342}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.34,0:03:17.26,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:196342,197260}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.26,0:03:19.05,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:197260,199053}A name for her.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.05,0:03:20.63,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:199053,200638}Not bad, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.63,0:03:21.43,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:200638,201431}Uhm…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.43,0:03:22.34,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:201431,202348}It's not good?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.34,0:03:23.64,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:202348,203641}Well…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.68,0:03:28.39,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:204684,208396}If I had to guess from\Nthe patches, she's a Collie, so…{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.35,0:03:35.65,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:209355,215653}She may become much larger\Nwhen she grows up.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.57,0:03:39.19,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:216571,219198}Calling a huge dog "Shorty"\Nwould be rather odd.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.07,0:03:42.16,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:221075,222160}I'm going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.62,0:03:48.29,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:227623,228291}John?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.29,0:03:49.12,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:228291,229125}Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.70,0:03:51.50,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:229709,231502}About this puppy…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.21,0:03:54.13,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:232211,234130}Make sure you tell\Nyour mother about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.00,0:03:56.00,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:235006,236007}Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.59,0:03:57.50,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:236591,237508}See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.67,0:04:06.26,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:241679,246267}Also don't just focus on the puppy,\Nmake sure you eat your meal as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.85,0:04:09.06,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:246851,249061}This soup is really salty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.06,0:04:10.64,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:249061,250646}Did I put too much seasoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.52,0:04:14.52,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:251522,254525}Try to put some sugar in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.19,0:04:16.52,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:255193,256527}All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.45,0:04:23.74,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:262450,263743}Now it's so sweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.21,0:04:38.42,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:277215,278424}This is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.60,0:04:54.27,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:291604,294273}There it is! I was wearing it\Nwhen I was three.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.52,0:04:59.61,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:297527,299612}This is your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.61,0:05:01.03,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:299612,301030}You'll stay here for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.57,0:05:03.44,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:301572,303449}Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.44,0:05:08.16,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:303449,308162}When I get back from school,\Nwe'll look your real home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.74,0:05:13.79,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:310748,313793}All right, I have to go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.87,0:05:16.62,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:314877,316629}Just stay there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.33,0:05:18.63,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:317338,318631}I'll be back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.71,0:05:27.22,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:323719,327223}Today someone finally\Nanswered me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:44.57,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:343698,344574}Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.57,0:05:46.24,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:344574,346242}Good morning, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.95,0:05:49.70,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:347952,349704}I remembered, yesterday, Colin…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:50.74,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:349704,350746}John!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.74,0:05:52.54,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:350746,352540}Oh? Sandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.54,0:05:55.41,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:352540,355418}This is not the way to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.41,0:05:58.21,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:355418,358212}I wanted to walk today\Ninstead of riding a bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.21,0:06:00.71,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:358212,360715}Say, did the puppy drink the milk?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.71,0:06:02.04,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:360715,362049}Yes, she did.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.04,0:06:03.84,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:362049,363843}John!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.84,0:06:06.97,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:363843,366971}Did the puppy drink the milk?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.97,0:06:08.47,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:366971,368472}Oh? Colin, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.47,0:06:09.43,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:368472,369432}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:12.10,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:370182,372101}I got a baby bottle from Colin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.10,0:06:12.93,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:372101,372935}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.56,0:06:15.31,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:373561,375313}She drank a lot, Colin!{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.31,0:06:16.56,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:375313,376564}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.56,0:06:20.27,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:377565,380276}This is fantastic.\NShe drank it.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.27,0:06:21.06,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:380276,381068}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.40,0:06:24.69,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:381402,384697}Remember, you promised me\Nthat I could see the puppy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.69,0:06:26.40,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:384697,386407}Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.40,0:06:28.57,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:386407,388576}Let's go see her\Ntoday after school.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.62,0:06:32.45,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:390620,392455}But even if she's just a puppy,{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.45,0:06:36.20,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:392455,396208}she's big enough to\Ndrink from a plate.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.20,0:06:37.16,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:396208,397168}You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.16,0:06:39.96,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:397168,399962}So, what do you call\Nthat spoiled little guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.29,0:06:41.92,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:400296,401923}What? Spoiled?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.92,0:06:45.55,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:401923,405551}Yeah. Dogs are like their owners.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.55,0:06:48.93,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:405551,408930}Doesn't she remind you\Nof certain someone?{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.93,0:06:52.39,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:408930,412391}Wait, what?\NYou think I'm spoiled? Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.39,0:06:54.81,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:412391,414810}Also, I'm not her owner.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.81,0:06:57.22,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:414810,417229}I'm just protecting her,\Nbecause she's lost.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:49.59,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:524336,529592}My goodness. Being up\Nfor two days straight is no joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.67,0:08:52.67,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:530676,532678}Hello, Melissa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.09,0:08:58.18,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:535097,538184}You caught me making\Na spectacle of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.18,0:08:59.68,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:538184,539685}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.68,0:09:02.98,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:539685,542980}First you had a delivery,\Nthen an operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.98,0:09:07.10,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:542980,547109}The Lord will forgive you\Na yawn or two, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.61,0:09:12.61,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:547610,552615}If something was to happen to you, everyone in\NGreenall Bridge would face a big problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.36,0:09:16.07,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:553365,556077}You're dead right.\NI shouldn't burden myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.07,0:09:19.62,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:556077,559622}You know where Dr. Hopper\Nwent right after, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.37,0:09:24.29,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:560372,564293}He's probably sleeping.\NAs expected of the great doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.29,0:09:28.54,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:564293,568547}And you know what he told me?\NThat when he wakes up, he'll go fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.54,0:09:29.38,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:568547,569381}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.09,0:09:34.13,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:571092,574136}That old man sure knows\Nhow to take it easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.30,0:09:38.01,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:574303,578015}All right then,\NI also better go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.01,0:09:38.97,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:578015,578974}Good idea, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:40.14,lassie default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{TIME:578974,580142}– Bye!\N– Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.85,0:09:45.94,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:580851,585940}Let's put appearances aside for a day\Nand get a good night's sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.94,0:09:49.19,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:585940,589193}I can clean and cook later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.40,0:09:54.19,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:591403,594198}Oh, this is heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.49,0:09:59.03,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:596492,599036}I don't want to move anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.03,0:10:02.62,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:599036,602623}I wonder if I can stay\Nthat way until evening?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.58,0:10:05.70,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:604583,605709}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.96,0:10:11.46,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:609964,611465}Is someone there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.92,0:10:57.88,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:655926,657887}Who are you?
Comment: 0,0:11:00.05,0:11:00.05,[chapter],[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:660055,660055}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.44,0:11:11.65,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:670441,671650}Five.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.65,0:11:12.69,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:671650,672693}Four.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.69,0:11:13.86,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:672693,673861}Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.86,0:11:15.02,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:673861,675029}Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.02,0:11:16.53,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:675029,676530}One.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.21,0:11:31.21,lassie default,Children,0,0,0,,{TIME:689210,691212}– Goodbye!\N– I'll go first!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.17,0:11:34.04,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:692171,694048}Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.94,0:11:53.73,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:711941,713734}A little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:04.49,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:721533,724495}Good. You're all clean now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.41,0:12:10.29,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:725412,730292}But what about the blanket?\NI have to wash it, too…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.46,0:12:12.67,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:731460,732670}I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.67,0:12:14.12,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:732670,734129}Sandy! Colin!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.12,0:12:15.17,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:734129,735172}Wait a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.17,0:12:16.21,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:735172,736215}John?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.38,0:12:21.13,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:737383,741136}Oops, Mom was working the\Nnight shift and is already back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.13,0:12:23.88,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:741136,743889}Ah! Hey! Hey, little one!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.88,0:12:27.05,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:743889,747059}Oh, don't get near it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.05,0:12:28.14,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:747059,748143}John!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.01,0:12:30.35,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:749019,750354}Hello, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.35,0:12:33.23,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:750354,753232}Oh? Looks like she likes you.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.27,0:12:38.07,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:754275,758070}Take her and dry her,\Nthen give her something to eat.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.07,0:12:40.90,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:758070,760906}I have to finish here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.90,0:12:42.44,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:760906,762449}What are you washing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.32,0:12:45.99,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:763325,765995}Ah! It was her!{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.49,0:12:47.91,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:766495,767913}I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.91,0:12:51.33,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:767913,771333}No, it's fine, you have to warm\Nher up near the fireplace.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.54,0:12:54.54,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:772543,774545}See? She'll get cold.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.54,0:12:58.59,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:774545,778590}No, if you do this, Mom,\NI'll do the washing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.59,0:13:02.34,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:778590,782344}Come on, you look like\Nyou're gonna fall asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.22,0:13:04.93,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:783220,784930}But what about your guests?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:05.59,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:784930,785597}Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.30,0:13:08.55,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:787308,788559}Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.55,0:13:10.60,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:788559,790602}We could heard most of it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.39,0:13:13.93,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:791395,793939}We'd better go home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.48,0:13:16.85,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:795482,796859}See you…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.65,0:13:19.36,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:797651,799361}I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.82,0:13:22.61,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:800821,802614}I wanted to see the puppy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.61,0:13:24.11,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:802614,804116}Hey, no complaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.11,0:13:26.28,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:804116,806285}It wasn't the best time for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.33,0:13:33.33,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:811332,813334}So warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.04,0:13:36.17,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:814043,816170}What a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.17,0:13:39.63,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:816170,819631}Looks like I reached\Nmy limit for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.96,0:13:42.84,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:821967,822843}Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.21,0:13:46.34,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:824219,826347}Well, I'll gladly accept your offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.49,0:14:07.61,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:846492,847618}John?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.45,0:14:12.49,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:849453,852498}What will you do with this puppy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.08,0:14:15.37,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:853082,855376}What do you mean?{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.37,0:14:17.04,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:855376,857044}She's a lost puppy.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:19.67,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:857044,859671}I must find her real owner.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.67,0:14:23.59,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:859671,863592}But what if you don't find them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.59,0:14:26.47,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:863592,866470}Can you take care of her then?{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.97,0:14:32.93,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:868972,872935}Your mother is a nurse\Nand is too busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.68,0:14:38.52,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:873685,878524}Taking care of living creatures\Nis very hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.52,0:14:39.94,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:878524,879942}It isn't to be made light of.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.40,0:14:45.98,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:881402,885989}What happened today\Nis just the tip of the iceberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.98,0:14:50.95,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:885989,890953}You were one mischievous boy\Nwhen you were a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.16,0:14:55.12,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:892162,895124}You most likely don't remember it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.12,0:15:03.54,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:895124,903549}but I think the worst was that one time\Nwhen you had a terrible, terrible fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.54,0:15:07.26,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:903549,907261}Have you thought about\Nwhat's going to happen next?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.30,0:15:11.47,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:910305,911473}John?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.93,0:15:14.22,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:911932,914226}I don't know, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.22,0:15:18.14,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:914226,918147}For now I'll do my best\Nto find her owner.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.31,0:15:23.48,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:920315,923485}Sounds good.\NDo what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.77,0:15:27.11,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:923777,927114}I'm sure her owner\Nis worried sick about her.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.11,0:15:30.45,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:927114,930451}And her mother must want\Nto see her again.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.49,0:15:35.78,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:931493,935789}This is why I simply\Nmust find her owner.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.78,0:15:37.33,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:935789,937332}Am I right, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.41,0:16:21.54,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:980417,981543}Tears…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.04,0:16:25.38,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:984046,985380}Ah, hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.55,0:16:37.39,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:993555,997392}Now what does Mom usually put?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.39,0:16:38.60,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:997392,998602}Ah, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.41,0:17:02.25,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1018413,1022251}Sage and parsley…\NAnd what else?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.12,0:17:06.33,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1023126,1026338}It gets so tasty if you put these.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:13.01,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1031468,1033011}All right, that should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:24.18,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1039935,1044189}I'm sure Mom will be surprised\Nwhen she wakes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.67,0:18:39.01,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1116678,1119014}Hey, where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.14,0:18:45.77,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1124144,1125771}Grandma Forrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.14,0:18:48.10,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1126146,1128106}Have you seen a puppy here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.10,0:18:49.27,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1128106,1129274}About this size.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.44,0:18:53.61,lassie default,Grandma Forrester,0,0,0,,{TIME:1130442,1133612}Have you checked\Nat your home well?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.61,0:18:55.44,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1133612,1135447}I searched all over,\Nbut I couldn't find her!{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.23,0:19:01.78,lassie default,Grandma Forrester,0,0,0,,{TIME:1136239,1141787}I can see everything what happens\Non the main street from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.49,0:19:08.08,lassie default,Grandma Forrester,0,0,0,,{TIME:1142496,1148085}Yet I didn't see any puppy.\NAre you sure you searched well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.08,0:19:10.29,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1148085,1150295}Ah, right! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.71,0:19:16.42,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1152714,1156426}The backyard!\NMaybe it went outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.76,0:19:24.39,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1161765,1164393}How am I supposed to look for her?{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.90,0:19:37.03,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1171900,1177030}Like Mom just said, caring\Nfor living creatures is very hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.03,0:19:40.15,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:1177030,1180158}Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.61,0:19:43.07,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:1181618,1183078}Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.07,0:19:45.58,lassie default,Sandy's brother,0,0,0,,{TIME:1183078,1185580}Where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.70,0:19:52.12,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:1187708,1192129}Hey, Bingo!\NShow yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.12,0:19:54.38,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1192129,1194381}Sandy? What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.50,0:19:58.09,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:1195507,1198093}John, you know our Bingo, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:19:59.51,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:1198093,1199511}It's a sheep dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.51,0:20:01.80,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1199511,1201805}Has it gone missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.09,0:20:03.59,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:1202097,1203598}Yeah…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.59,0:20:06.60,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:1203598,1206601}All the sheep\Nhave returned, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.60,0:20:08.14,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1206601,1208145}Our puppy has gone missing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.14,0:20:09.18,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:1208145,1209187}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.18,0:20:10.98,lassie default,Sandy's brother,0,0,0,,{TIME:1209187,1210981}Ah, here he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.98,0:20:12.60,lassie default,Sandy's brother,0,0,0,,{TIME:1210981,1212607}He was here all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.60,0:20:15.44,lassie default,Sandy's brother,0,0,0,,{TIME:1212607,1215444}John, is this your puppy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.44,0:20:16.06,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1215444,1216069}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.82,0:20:21.07,lassie default,Sandy's brother,0,0,0,,{TIME:1216820,1221074}My goodness. Looks like the baby\Nfound one comfortable bed to sleep in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.45,0:20:24.53,lassie default,Sandy's brother,0,0,0,,{TIME:1221450,1224536}He can't move one foot like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.53,0:20:26.41,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:1224536,1226413}Told ya, spoiled little guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.41,0:20:27.08,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1226413,1227080}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.29,0:20:30.08,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1228290,1230083}I think I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.25,0:20:35.42,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1231251,1235422}You… missed your mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.42,0:20:36.38,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:1235422,1236381}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.38,0:20:38.59,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:1236381,1238592}But Bingo is just an old dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.59,0:20:42.22,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1238592,1242220}You're right.\NAnd she's still just a puppy.{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.05,0:20:48.18,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1243054,1248185}I'll definitely find your mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.98,0:20:57.23,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1253982,1257235}I think this is the place\Nwhere I found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.07,0:21:02.11,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1259070,1262115}I wonder if we can find any clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.99,0:21:07.12,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1264993,1267120}What's a boat doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.33,0:21:16.00,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1273335,1276004}A collar… Is this yours?
